{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4693].
  {panel}

It would be useful to have a custom field that recorded the number of times that an issue has been in a certain state.  For instance, one could tell how many times an issue has been reopened.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4679].
  {panel}

I would like the ability to give the permission to set a fix version separate from the permission to resolve.
That way a projectleader can schedule issues for a particular version, without having the ability to resolve them.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4665].
  {panel}

Currently, the Mail queue items dont survive an application restart.

The mail queue service recently got stuck with close to 1000 mails in it. (Not sure why - but something to do with our smtp server going down a week ago - the oldest mail queue items matched the smtp server crash date)

In order to rectify it, we had to restart the server - but in doing so we lost all the mails... grr!

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4663].
  {panel}

In the "Developer Workload Report", a developer is shown assigned to 4 issues. After clicking on his username link or on the number of issues link, he is shown assigned to 10 issues. 

It seems that only issues with a time estimate are listed in the Developer Workload Report.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4655].
  {panel}

It would be useful to have a workflow condition that passed if the current issue has a certain priority, or a priority above a certain level.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4646].
  {panel}

It is not possible to set a date to version from which on no more issues can be added to this version.
Better would be a 2 step workflow. After the first "planning end date" only issues with priority Critical or Blocker can be added. After the second deadline only Blocker-Issues can be added.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4641].
  {panel}

Users must perform a reindex after changing Custom Field Searcher types.

This is quite a hassle and might not actually get done anyway. Should be made automatic

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-4629].
  {panel}

Currently in JIRA, the 'summary' column claims 100% of available space.  This is fine, except when you have another textarea field like 'description', which needs as much if not more space.  We should work out a more sophisticated means of allocating column widths.
